---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Avoid Overpromising in Language and Branding"
  description="Use accurate, restrained language in product copy and branding—no 'always accurate', 'fully automated', or 'replaces human judgment' when the system has limits or requires human oversight."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Language and branding" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Accurate Claims</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >AI-assisted drafting: Get suggestions to speed up writing. Review and edit before you
            send—you're in control.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Describes assistance and user control; doesn't promise perfection or full automation.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Restrained Taglines</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >"Smarter drafts, faster" or "Suggestions that save time"—not "Perfect copy every time"
            or "AI that writes for you."</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Benefits are real (speed, help) without implying infallibility or full replacement of
            the user.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Overpromising (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >"100% accurate", "Fully automated decisions", "AI that thinks like you", "No need to
            review." Branding that suggests the AI replaces human judgment or never errs.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Users expect more than the system can deliver; trust is lost when reality doesn't match
            the promise.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Language to Avoid vs Prefer</b></mds-text>
          <div class="grid gap-300">
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Avoid:</b> "Always right", "Fully automated", "Replaces experts", "No review needed"</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Prefer:</b> "Assists", "Suggests", "Drafts for review", "Designed to help you"</mds-text
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Use language that reflects real capabilities: assist, suggest, draft, help—and that the user
      reviews or decides.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Claim always-accurate, fully automated, or no-review-needed when the system has limits or
      requires human oversight.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Align marketing and in-product copy with what the AI actually does and doesn't do.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Let branding promise more than the product delivers; avoid "replaces human judgment" or
      similar overclaims.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
